pageContext.claim: “I saved it again a number of months ago when oil was crashing because of the pandemic, we saved it. We got to say what you want about relationship. We got Saudi Arabia, Mexico, and Russia to cut back way back. We saved our oil industry and now it's very vibrant [Crosstalk] everybody has very inexpensive gasoline, remember that.”
pageContext.analysis: The president has little power to move prices at the gas pump in any direction because they depend on market forces beyond his control. A variety of market factors has contributed to the falling price of gasoline. None of them involves Trump’s phone calls to foreign leaders in oil-rich countries.
